Epic 1: Dashboard Main View Enhancement
User Story 1.1: Complete Dashboard Layout and Welcome Section
As a Data Quality Manager
I want a comprehensive dashboard with proper layout and welcome messaging
So that I can quickly understand my data management work status and navigate the platform effectively
Acceptance Criteria:

Dashboard displays "Dashboard" as the main heading (large, bold)
Welcome message reads: "Welcome back! Here's what's happening with your data management work."
Top navigation bar includes:

AI4DM logo with tagline "AI Agents for Data Management" (left-aligned)
Dashboard button (active/selected state with home icon)
Chat button with icon
Knowledge Bases button with icon
Version number "v2.0.0" (right-aligned)


Navigation buttons use gradient styling (blue to purple)
Dashboard content area is properly spaced with white/light background

Main Flow:

User logs into AI4DM platform
System displays Dashboard as default landing page
Dashboard loads with all components visible
User sees welcome message at top
User can access all navigation options from top bar

Alternative Flow:

If user arrives from another section, Dashboard button shows active state
If no data available, system displays appropriate empty state messages

Tasks and Subtasks:
Task 1.1.1: Implement Dashboard Header Section

Subtask 1: Add "Dashboard" h1 heading with proper typography (font-size: 48-56px, font-weight: bold)
Subtask 2: Add welcome message as subtitle (font-size: 18-20px, gray color)
Subtask 3: Ensure proper spacing between heading and content (margin-bottom: 32-40px)
Subtask 4: Test responsive behavior on different screen sizes

Task 1.1.2: Build Top Navigation Bar

Subtask 1: Create navigation container with proper height (64-72px)
Subtask 2: Implement AI4DM logo component with purple gradient background
Subtask 3: Add "AI Agents for Data Management" tagline below logo
Subtask 4: Create Dashboard button with home icon and active state styling
Subtask 5: Create Chat button with message icon
Subtask 6: Create Knowledge Bases button with book icon
Subtask 7: Add version number display on far right
Subtask 8: Apply gradient styling (blue #2196F3 to purple #9C27B0) to active navigation button
Subtask 9: Implement hover states for all navigation buttons
Subtask 10: Test navigation functionality and active state management


User Story 1.2: Notifications Panel Implementation
As a Data Quality Manager
I want a comprehensive notifications panel on my dashboard
So that I can stay informed about important updates, deadlines, and requests
Acceptance Criteria:

Notifications panel displays on left side of dashboard
Panel header shows "Notifications" title with bell icon
Unread count displays prominently (e.g., "1 unread")
"Clear All" button appears in top-right of panel
Each notification card shows:

Appropriate icon (email, chart, bell, etc.)
Notification title
Description text
Sender/source name
Timestamp (e.g., "2h ago")
Priority badge (HIGH, MEDIUM) with color coding


Notifications are properly ordered by priority and timestamp
Selected/active notification has visible left border highlight
Minimum 3-4 notification cards visible

Main Flow:

User views dashboard
System displays notifications panel on left side
User sees unread count at top
User can scroll through notifications
User can click individual notifications to view details
User can clear all notifications via button

Alternative Flow:

If no unread notifications, show "0 unread" or hide count
If no notifications exist, show empty state message
If notification clicked, mark as read and update count

Tasks and Subtasks:
Task 1.2.1: Create Notifications Panel Container

Subtask 1: Design panel with white background and subtle border
Subtask 2: Set fixed width (approximately 600-650px)
Subtask 3: Add proper padding (24-32px)
Subtask 4: Implement rounded corners (8-12px border-radius)
Subtask 5: Add subtle shadow for depth

Task 1.2.2: Build Notifications Header

Subtask 1: Create header section with bell icon (blue/purple color)
Subtask 2: Add "Notifications" title (font-size: 24-28px, font-weight: 600)
Subtask 3: Implement unread counter badge (blue text, small font)
Subtask 4: Add "Clear All" button (right-aligned, gray text with hover state)
Subtask 5: Ensure proper spacing between elements

Task 1.2.3: Implement Individual Notification Cards

Subtask 1: Create notification card component with proper layout
Subtask 2: Add icon container (left side, 40x40px, with background color matching notification type)
Subtask 3: Implement notification title (font-size: 16-18px, font-weight: 600)
Subtask 4: Add description text (font-size: 14px, gray color, line-height: 1.5)
Subtask 5: Create sender/timestamp footer (font-size: 12-13px, lighter gray)
Subtask 6: Add priority badge (HIGH: red background, MEDIUM: orange background)
Subtask 7: Implement left border highlight for selected state (4px solid, blue)
