User Story 1.3: Upcoming Assessments Panel Implementation
As a Data Quality Manager
I want an upcoming assessments panel on my dashboard
So that I can track upcoming deadlines, priorities, and assessment statuses
Acceptance Criteria:

Upcoming Assessments panel displays on right side of dashboard
Panel header shows "Upcoming Assessments" with calendar icon
Count of due items displays (e.g., "3 due soon")
Each assessment card shows:

Appropriate icon (chart, checkmark, governance icon)
Assessment title
Due date with calendar icon (e.g., "Due in 1 weeks")
Assignee with user icon (shows "Current User")
Priority with icon (High Priority: red, Medium Priority: orange)
Status badge (In Progress: blue, Not Started: yellow)


Assessment cards are properly spaced and organized
At least 3 assessment cards visible
One assessment has golden/yellow highlight border

Main Flow:

User views dashboard
System displays upcoming assessments on right side
User sees count of assessments due soon
User can view details of each assessment
User can click assessment to view full details
User sees visual priority and status indicators

Alternative Flow:

If no upcoming assessments, show empty state
If assessment clicked, navigate to assessment detail view
If assessment overdue, show different styling

