Epic 3: AI Agent Chat Interface Enhancement
User Story 3.1: Complete AI Agent Context Chat Interface
As a Data Quality Manager
I want an AI agent chat interface with active context management
So that I can collaborate with the AI on my assessment work with full context awareness
Acceptance Criteria:

Chat interface displays with proper header:

Title: "AI Agent - DQ Assessment PMO"
Document context: "Section 3 Draft • Last edited 15 min ago"
"Active Context" badge (white, rounded)
"Change" button (right side)


AI welcome message displays:

"Welcome back! I've loaded your PMO Data Quality Assessment context. You were working on Section 3: Data Governance Framework."
"Current progress: 65% complete. Would you like to continue where you left off?"


User message displays in dark bubble (right-aligned):

"Yes, let's continue with Section 3. Can you show me what we have so far?"


AI response shows Section 3 content in detailed card format:

Section number and title
Key components in bullet points
Key findings text
"Draft - Section Incomplete" status badge (red, at bottom)


Action options displayed at bottom:

"Continue Draft" button (left)
"Agent Send" toggle (right, with radio button)


Suggested Actions section with four buttons:

"Add Metrics Table" (with table icon)
"Review SharePoint Docs" (with document icon)
"Generate Recommendations" (with lightbulb icon)
"Create Summary" (with document icon)


Message input box at bottom with "Ask about this assessment or continue drafting..." placeholder
"Send" button (right side of input)

Main Flow:

User clicks to open chat interface for assessment
System loads AI Agent chat with active context
AI displays welcome message with context information
User responds to continue work
AI shows current section content
User sees suggested actions and can choose next steps
User can type new messages or select suggested actions

Alternative Flow:

If no active context, prompt user to select workstream
If context changed, show update notification
If draft auto-saved, show notification

